/* Python wrapper */

 0535:         We minimize
 0536:         (1/2) * w^T Q w - q^T w + alpha norm(w, 1) + (beta/2) * norm(w, 2)^2

 0872:     """Cython version of the coordinate descent algorithm
 0873:         for Elastic-Net regression
 0874:         We minimize
 0875:         (1/2) * norm(y - X w, 2)^2 + alpha norm(w, 1) + (beta/2) norm(w, 2)^2
 0876:     """
 0877: 
 0878:     # fused types version of BLAS functions
 0879:     cdef DOT dot
 0880:     cdef AXPY axpy
 0881:     cdef ASUM asum

 1473: #@cython.boundscheck(False)
 1474: #@cython.wraparound(False)
 1475: #@cython.cdivision(True)
 1476: #def enet_coordinate_descent_multi_task_adaptive(double[::1, :] W, double[:] l1_reg,
 1477: #                                       double l2_reg,
 1478: #                                       np.ndarray[double, ndim=2, mode='fortran'] X,
 1479: #                                       np.ndarray[double, ndim=2] Y,
 1480: #                                       int max_iter, double tol, object rng,
 1481: #                                       bint random=0):
 1482: #    """Cython version of the coordinate descent algorithm
 1483: #        for Elastic-Net mult-task regression
 1484: #        We minimize
 1485: #        (1/2) * norm(y - X w, 2)^2 + l1_reg ||w||_21 + (1/2) * l2_reg norm(w, 2)^2
 1486: #    """
 1487: #    # get the data information into easy vars
 1488: #    cdef unsigned int n_samples = X.shape[0]
 1489: #    cdef unsigned int n_features = X.shape[1]
 1490: #    cdef unsigned int n_tasks = Y.shape[1]
 1491: #
 1492: #    # to store XtA
 1493: #    cdef double[:, ::1] XtA = np.zeros((n_features, n_tasks))
 1494: #    cdef double XtA_axis1norm
 1495: #    cdef double dual_norm_XtA
 1496: #
